            <title>[OAK-8130] Index corruption stats should get updated also when no failing index remains</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-8130</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;TrackingCorruptIndexHandler&lt;/tt&gt; uses a &lt;tt&gt;MeterStats&lt;/tt&gt; to record index corruptions, however it wrongly avoids updating the stats when the failing indexes &lt;tt&gt;Map&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is empty, thus leading to the stats not being 0 again if a corruption happens.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
